messageBody:
Moira O'Brien wrote:
>
>
> Paul, I didn't mean to demean the work you are doing. It is great stuff
> and I am sure the whole group is grateful for all the time and effort
> you are putting into it. If I had the expertise I would contribute more
> to it, but I dont.
>
> regards
>
> 
>
> PS What happened to the namer dot in ThothUni?
>

Hi Moira,

I never got the feeling that you demeaned anything I did, so don't worry
about that. Are you referring to the group post about the letters or
this thread?

I didn't put a naming dot in ThothUni because Unicode has its own dot,
or really several sets of dots. I use one of these dots for the news,
but you can't see it too well, and last night I realized I should be
using character U+00B7, or what is the bullet. I can copy this character
to where the QS letters are if that will make things easier. What is
this keyboard you are talking about that types in Unicode directly? That
sounds nice.

Paul

PS The QS you are posting is not appearing as QS letters in my email. It
just is so hard to get that working.
